The journey towards having a common currency in the East Africa region is fast gaining momentum with plans underway by the east Africa community to set up a monetary institute being in the works. If successful this will mean, Kenya, Uganda, Rwanda, Burundi and South Sudan operating under a single currency a venture touted as a major milestone towards regional integration. KTN's deputy economics affairs editor Aby Agina had an interview with the new EACC secretary general dr. Peter Mathuki.